\par \pard\plain \s27\sb120\widctlpar\tx270 \b\f5\fs18 How to statically link dbExpress drivers
\par \pard\plain \widctlpar\tx270 \f4\fs20 
\par Static linking of dbExpress drivers (dbxdsnint.lib for InterBase, dbxdsnora.lib for Oracle, dbxdsndb2.lib for DB2, or dbxdsnmys.lib for MySQL 3.23.x) in C++Builder is a two-step process: Link the driver, then register both the driver and the DataSnap libr
ary. You can enter this code in your TForm constructor.
\par The .lib files are located in your \\cbuilder6\\lib directory. 
\par 
\par \pard\plain \s16\fi-270\li270\widctlpar\tx270 \f4\fs20 {\b\i Important: }{\i 
\par }\tab Do not link more than one dbExpress driver into a project. Linking more than one driver will cause linking errors and may require a corrective shutdown of C++Builder.
\par \pard\plain \widctlpar\tx270 \f4\fs20 
\par The following example uses the InterBase driver.
\par 
\par {\b Step 1.}  Include the dbExpress/DataSnap header file:
\par \pard\plain \s15\widctlpar\tx270 \f11\fs20 
\par #include <dbxdsnint.h>
\par \pard\plain \widctlpar\tx270 \f4\fs20  
\par {\b Step 2.} Register the static library:
\par 
\par \pard\plain \s15\widctlpar\tx270 \f11\fs20 RegisterDbXpressLib(::getSQLDriverINTERBASE);
\par RegisterMidasLib(::DllGetClassObject);
\par \pard\plain \widctlpar\tx270 \f4\fs20 
\par \pard\plain \s16\fi-270\li270\widctlpar\tx270 \f4\fs20 {\b\i Note: }{\i 
\par }\tab DataSnap (a part of what was formerly known as MIDAS) is linked in to each dbExpress driver for C++Builder 6. Thus, if you need to statically link DataSnap only for access to midaslib, simply link in any of the drivers listed above.
\par \pard\plain \widctlpar\tx270 \f4\fs20 
\par \pard\plain \s27\sb120\widctlpar\tx270 \b\f5\fs18 Updating existing dbExpress configuration files
\par \pard\plain \widctlpar\tx270 \f4\fs20 
\par If the shared dbExpress configuration files dbxconnections.ini and dbxdrivers.ini already exist (default location \\Program Files\\Common Files\\Borland Shared\\DBExpress), C++Builder w
ill not overwrite them. Instead, it will install updated configuration files named dbxconnections.win and dbxdrivers.win into the same location as the existing configuration files. To use the new configuration information, first back up the existing .ini 
files, then manually merge the new data (using any text editor) from the .win files into the .ini files. 
\par 
\par {\b Important note for Informix users}: If you have Delphi 6 installed, you will need to merge the Informix information from the dbx*.win files into your dbx*.ini files, as described above.
\par 
