\par \pard\plain \s27\sb120\widctlpar\tx270 \b\f5\fs18 InterBase 6 Dialect 3
\par \pard\plain \widctlpar\tx270 \f4\fs20 
\par To use the new InterBase 6 or 6.5 Dialect 3 features, add an entry to your Windows registry under
\par \pard\plain \s15\widctlpar\tx270 \f11\fs20 \tab HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\
\par \tab \tab Borland\\Database Engine\\Settings
\par \tab \tab \\Drivers\\Intrbase\\Db Open\\SQLDIALECT 
\par \pard\plain \widctlpar\tx270 \f4\fs20 and set the value to "3". 
\par 
\par When an InterBase alias is created, the new entry will be available in the .CFG file. 
\par 
\par To use InterBase 5.6, SQLDIALECT can be set to "1" (existing IB aliases which do not have the SQLDIALECT entry default to SQLDIALECT=1 or to the registry setting when the SQLDIALECT entry is added to the registry). 
\par 
\par \pard\plain \s27\sb120\widctlpar\tx270 \b\f5\fs18 Informix BLOB/CLOB fields
\par \pard\plain \widctlpar\tx270 \f4\fs20 
\par A new global variable, InformixLob, is available to allow you to work with Informix BLOB and CLOB fields.
\par 
\par The variable is required because Informix BLOB (fldBLOB, fldstHBINARY) and CLOB (fldBLOB, fldstHMEMO) fields are mapped as ftOraBlob and ftOraClob, respectively, and the DataSnap resolver performs special query generation when resolving Oracle BLOB/CLOB f
ields, but not when resolving Informix BLOB/CLOBs. To address this issue, set InformixLob to True when using Informix BLOB/CLOBs, and switch it back to False (the default) when using Oracle BLOB/CLOBs.
\par 
\par \pard\plain \s27\sb120\widctlpar\tx270 \b\f5\fs18 Oracle LONG and LONG RAW fields
\par \pard\plain \widctlpar\tx270 \f4\fs20 
\par When using Oracle, the size of LONG and LONG RAW fields cannot be determined without fetching the whole field. So if BLOB SIZE is set to -1, LONG and LONG RAW fields are truncated to 64K. Recommendation: Set BLOB SIZE to your best estimate of the blob siz
e.
\par 
